No fewer than 30 persons suspected to be members of different secret cults have been arrested by the Edo State Command of the Nigeria Police. Parading the suspects before journalists on Thursday, Edo State Police Command spokesman Chidi Nwanbuzor, a superintendent of police gave the breakdown of the suspects to include seven females and 23 males He said arising from police concerted efforts to rid the state of the menace of cultism, the command carried out a raid in the various black spots across the state and arrested the 30 suspects. He said over 60 suspects have been arrested since the outbreak of cult-related killings in the state in the past two weeks. He further explained that most of the suspects were arrested in New Benin and Siluko road axis in the Benin metropolis. The command image maker, said Abutu Yaro, the commissioner in charge of the state, vowed to make the state unhabitable for criminal elements. He added that the commissioner warned criminal elements to repent or vacate the state for their own interest and benefits.